# LAIRS & SentiNet Architecture (Public Overview)

This document describes the public, high-level architecture for the LAIRS & SentiNet platform. It focuses on structure, governance, and system boundaries. It intentionally omits production implementation details, keys, and deployable configurations.

---

## 1) Platform at a Glance

LAIRS is the cognitive runtime (memory, identity, orchestration).
SentiNet is the secure fabric (zones, default-deny segmentation, internal DNS/PKI).

[ Human Master Admin ]
|
v
+------------------------------+
| LAIRS (Mind) |
| - Runtime / Orchestration |
| - Memory + Identity |
| - Policy Hooks + Audit |
+--------------+---------------+
|
v
+------------------------------+
| SentiNet (Fabric) |
| - Zones + Default-Deny |
| - Internal DNS + PKI |
| - Controlled Bridge Modes |
+------+-----------------------+
|
v
+------------------------------+
| Sentinel Modules (Products) |
| AGENT | Gate | AV | Forge|
+------------------------------+


---

## 2) LAIRS Core (Cognitive Runtime)

LAIRS is a governed intelligence substrate. Models are treated as replaceable cognitive engines; governance and auditability are first-class.

+--------------------------------------------------+

LAIRS Brain
Session + Identity Manager
Policy Hooks / Authorization Gates
Tool & Action Router
Model Orchestrator (specialists + generalists)
Memory Interfaces
Audit Log / Event Ledger
+---------------------+----------------------------+
                  |
                  v
 +----------------+------------------+
 |                                   |
 v                                   v
+------------+ +----------------+
| State Store| | Vector Memory |
| (configs, | | (retrieval) |
| profiles) | +----------------+
+------------+ +----------------+
|
v
+----------------+
| Append-only |
| Event/Audit Log|
+----------------+


Key idea: **LAIRS governs actions** through policy gates and produces **verifiable evidence** via audit logs.

---

## 3) SentiNet Fabric (Security + Identity + Zones)

SentiNet provides environment-level safety: segmentation, service identity, and controlled ingress/egress.

                 +----------------------+
                 |   Controlled Bridge  |
                 |  (Mode B / Mode A)   |
                 +----------+-----------+
                            |
                            v
+----------------------------------------------------------------+

SentiNet Zones
Zone 1: Core / Control -> LAIRS Brain + Governance
Zone 2: Security Services -> Gate, Watchdog, AV
Zone 3: Workloads/Apps -> User services, integrations
Zone 4: Edge/IoT/Endpoints -> Agents, sensors, devices
----------------------------------------------------------------
Default-Deny VLAN Segmentation + Service Identity (mTLS)
Internal DNS + PKI (cert issuance/rotation model)
+----------------------------------------------------------------+


SentiNet ensures:
- **default-deny** network posture
- **service identity** (cert-backed)
- **policy-enforced** flows between zones

---

