---

## 5) Governance Flow (Human Root Authority)

This is the platformâ€™s non-negotiable safety model: the system may propose actions, but critical changes require explicit human authorization.

(Observation) -> (Analysis) -> (Proposal) -> (Approval) -> (Apply) -> (Verify)

+-----------+ +----------+ +-----------+ +-----------+ +--------+
| AGENT | -> | LAIRS | -> | Forge | -> | Human | -> | Apply |
| Gate / AV | | Reasoning| | Proposal | | Master | | (reboot|
+-----------+ +----------+ +-----------+ | Admin | | boundary|
+-----------+ +--------+
|
v
+---------------+
| Audit Evidence |
| + Rollback |
+---------------+


Principle: **No autonomous system modification.** The system can generate and test patches, but application requires human approval and controlled staging with rollback.

---

## 6) Repository Scope

This repository contains:
- public architecture descriptions
- diagrams and governance model
- module boundaries and system concepts

This repository does not contain:
- production code or binaries
- cryptographic keys or signing material
- deployment configs intended for real environments

Core implementations are maintained separately under controlled licensing.

